55. D. Iam hercle ego illunc ammata] Plautus here alludes, in all probability, to a privilege accorded by the laws of the XII. Tables to creditors. In virtue of this any one who had a claim against another might, if the legal evidence were defective, proceed to the house os his debtor and publicly demand payment in loud and abusive language, so as to bring shame upon the defaulter among his neigh- 'bours Thus Festus s. v. Vagutatro, p. 375, ed. Muli, “ Vagutatia iu L. XII. signfficat quaestionem cum convicio. Cui testzmam‘um desuerit, is tertzii dz'ebus ob portum obvagulatum ito,·” and again, s. v.
